# ============================================================================
# template-default.env - Environment Configuration Template v2.1
# ============================================================================
# DESCRIPTION:
#   Universal template for Windows development environments with Scoop
#   Supports 40+ technologies and development tools
#
# USAGE:
#   1. Copy this file to:
#      - system.default.env           (system-wide, requires admin)
#      - system.HOSTNAME.USERNAME.env (system + host-specific)
#      - user.default.env             (user-specific, RECOMMENDED)
#      - user.HOSTNAME.USERNAME.env   (user + host-specific)
#
#   2. Remove # from lines you want to activate
#   3. Adjust paths to match your installation
#   4. Test with: .\scoop-boot.ps1 --apply-env --dry-run
#   5. Apply with: .\scoop-boot.ps1 --apply-env
#
# LOAD ORDER (later files override earlier ones):
#   1. system.default.env
#   2. system.HOSTNAME.USERNAME.env
#   3. user.default.env
#   4. user.HOSTNAME.USERNAME.env (HIGHEST PRIORITY)
#
# ============================================================================
# SYNTAX REFERENCE
# ============================================================================
#
# SET VARIABLES:
#   VAR_NAME=value                    # Set variable
#   VAR_NAME=$OTHER_VAR\path          # With variable expansion
#
# PATH MANIPULATION:
#   PATH+=C:\path                     # Prepend to PATH (add at beginning)
#   PATH=+C:\path                     # Append to PATH (add at end)
#   PATH-=C:\path                     # Remove from PATH
#   PATH -= C:\path                   # Alternative syntax
#
# REMOVE VARIABLES:
#   -VAR_NAME                         # Delete variable
#
# VARIABLE EXPANSION:
#   $SCOOP                            # Expands to your Scoop path (e.g., C:\usr)
#   $VAR_NAME                         # Reference other environment variables
#   ${VAR_NAME}                       # Alternative syntax (in strings)
#
# COMMENTS:
#   # This line is a comment
#   VAR=value  # Inline comment
#
# ============================================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. $SCOOP is automatically set based on your Scoop installation
# 2. Use $SCOOP instead of hardcoded paths for portability
# 3. PATH entries are checked for existence when applying
# 4. Backups are created automatically before changes
# 5. Shell restart required after applying changes!
#
# ============================================================================

